Version Control System (VCS) allows you to :
1) Revert files to previous state
2) Compare changes over time
3) See who modified what

GitHub is a web hosting service for project that use Git.
Git and GitHub are different things.
You can use Git without using GitHub.

Why Git?
1) Not centralised
2) No single point of failure or bottleneck


Git workflow:
1) You modify files in your working directory
2) You stage the files by adding them to your staging area
3) You do a commit,which takes the files as they are in the staging area and stores that snapshot
   permanently to your Git directory.